This paper deals with face verification using deep convolutional networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of one-shot learning and different model architectures and loss functions suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions detecting image forgeries, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the use of ophthalmic surgery images suggests a potential focus on medical imaging (cs.IR).
